__bs__ So I &apos;m a neurosurgeon .
__bs__ And like most of my colleagues , I have to deal , every day , with human tragedies .
__bs__ I realize how your life can change from one second to the other after a major stroke or after a car accident .
__bs__ And what is very frustrating for us neurosurgeons is to realize that unlike other organs of the body , the brain has very little ability for self-repair .
__bs__ And after a major injury of your central nervous system , the patients often remain with a severe handicap .
__bs__ And that &apos;s probably the reason why I &apos;ve chosen to be a functional neurosurgeon .
__bs__ What is a functional neurosurgeon ?
__bs__ It &apos;s a doctor who is trying to improve a neurological function through different surgical strategies .
__bs__ You &apos;ve certainly heard of one of the famous ones called deep brain stimulation , where you implant an electrode in the depths of the brain in order to modulate a circuit of neurons to improve a neurological function .
__bs__ It &apos;s really an amazing technology in that it has improved the destiny of patients with Parkinson &apos;s disease , with severe tremor , with severe pain .
__bs__ However , neuromodulation does not mean neuro-repair .
__bs__ And the dream of functional neurosurgeons is to repair the brain .
__bs__ I think that we are approaching this dream .
__bs__ And I would like to show you that we are very close to this .
__bs__ And that with a little bit of help , the brain is able to help itself .
__bs__ So the story started 15 years ago .
__bs__ At that time , I was a chief resident working days and nights in the emergency room .
__bs__ I often had to take care of patients with head trauma .
__bs__ You have to imagine that when a patient comes in with a severe head trauma , his brain is swelling and he &apos;s increasing his intracranial pressure .
__bs__ And in order to save his life , you have to decrease this intracranial pressure .
__bs__ And to do that , you sometimes have to remove a piece of swollen brain .
__bs__ So instead of throwing away these pieces of swollen brain , we decided with Jean-François Brunet , who is a colleague of mine , a biologist , to study them .
__bs__ What do I mean by that ?
__bs__ We wanted to grow cells from these pieces of tissue .
__bs__ It &apos;s not an easy task .
__bs__ Growing cells from a piece of tissue is a bit the same as growing very small children out from their family .
